                <td width="186" valign="top" class="row1" nowrap> <span class="largetext"><a name="6991"></a><b>Number6</b></span><br>
                  <span class="smalltext">Not a Number!<br>
                  <img src="images/avatars/gallery/gallery7/stewie1.gif" alt="" border="0" /><br>
                  <br>
                  Joined: 23 Jul 2002<br>
                  Posts: 298<br>
                  </span></td>
                <td valign="top" class="row1"> <span class="smalltext"><b>Vae Inimicus website helpful hints</b></span>
                  <p><span class="largetext">Since many folks are new, and may not be used to phpBB, I thought I’d give a brief overview of some features of this site.
<br />

<br />
1.	Did you know you could change the entire color scheme of the site? You have three “skins” to choose from. phpVB2 is the default one, in tan and blue. subSilver is in a brushed blue with lots of whitespace and VIBlack is a black theme with white text. You can change your board skin under your profile.
<br />

<br />
2.	You can send messages to others via the board. Click the “PM” link under a user’s name to send them a message. If you get a new PM, you can be notified by a pop up when you visit the site, or have the board send you an email. If you use a “popup stopper”, be aware that you won’t get the popup message, so please turn on email notification or at least just check your inbox once and a while!
<br />

<br />
3.	Lots of people use the “View Posts Since Last Visit” link on the portal page and on the Forum page to see new posts, instead of browsing from forum to forum.
<br />

<br />
4.	You can choose from a library of over 800 avatars. (Avatars are those little pictures under your name.) In your profile, click on the “Show Gallery” button, and then choose one of the Gallerys from the drop down list. 
<br />

<br />
5.	You can also link to a remote avatar, or you may upload one of your own to the server. That’s right, in your profile, you can browse to a local image and have it uploaded to the server for you to use. Be advised that remote hot-linking is forbidden on this server, so if you upload an image for use as an avatar, it will be viewed here on vaeinimicus.org just fine but if you try to link to that image from another message board, it will not appear. 
<br />

<br />
6.	You can comment on news stories in the News Forum. While not everyone can post news, anyone is able to comment on the stories there, as well as the Polls in the Polls forum.
<br />

<br />
7.	Set your local time zone! Do this under your profile. However, Daylight Savings Time is not supported, so it still might be off by an hour.
<br />

<br />
8.	If you are a VI member and want a vaeinimicus.org email address, just ask! I can set it to forward to some other email account, you can access the mail from the web or with a mail client. The choice is yours.
<br />

<br />
9.	Those little lines of text that appear under your name are called Titles. If you want something there, ask and maybe I can find something suitable.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Other random thoughts….
<br />

<br />
If you edit your own post within 10 minutes of posting it, an “Edited by soandso” message will not appear. However, if someone has already replied, an edited message will appear. Moderators and Admins do not leave “Edited By” messages at all.
<br />

<br />
HTML isn’t supported in the forums. However, you can use <a href="http://www.vaeinimicus.org/faq.php?mode=bbcode" target="_blank" class="postlink">BBCodes</a>!
<br />

<br />
That’s all for now. As always, please report any bugs or other weirdness to me via PM or something.<br />_________________<br />Number6</span><span class="smalltext"></span></p>
                </td>
              </tr>
